						<summary>

						<p>On a slab lying in the field of Shankarappa.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Bhūlōkamalla [Sōmēśvara III] 12th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This short and incomplete record engraved at the end of Inscription No. 86 above registers gifts of lands [probably to the god Rudrēśvara of <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> Gōraṇṭe] on the occasion of solar eclipse by Bhāskara bhattōpādhyāya, the preceptor of emperor Bhūlōkamalladēva. The gifted lands were measured in the measuring rod named <hi rend="italic">Samkēśvaradēvara kaiyyakōlu.</hi> Kōḷanūru (village) is mentioned at the end. It is in characters of the 12th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
